# circleci_project_environment_variable (Data Source)

Fetches information about a CircleCI project environment variable.

> **Note:** The CircleCI API returns a masked value for project environment variables. The `value` attribute will contain a masked string, not the actual secret value.

## Example Usage

```terraform
data "circleci_project_environment_variable" "example" {
  project_slug = "github/my-org/my-repo"
  name         = "MY_SECRET"
}
```

<!-- schema generated by tfplugindocs -->
## Schema

### Required

- `name` (String) The name of the environment variable.
- `project_slug` (String) The project slug in the format `vcs-type/org-name/repo-name`.

### Read-Only

- `created_at` (String) The timestamp when the environment variable was created.
- `value` (String, Sensitive) The masked value of the environment variable as returned by the API.
